Overview
On Day 2, we are setting up the technical foundation of the Furniture & Crockery Marketplace. This involves integrating essential frameworks, configuring APIs, and establishing a structured development environment. The goal is to ensure smooth scalability and a strong foundation for future enhancements.

Objectives
✅ Integrate backend frameworks and APIs for smooth data handling.
✅ Configure environment variables for secure data management.
✅ Establish database connectivity and define basic schemas.
✅ Set up reusable UI components for frontend development.

Progress
Backend Setup
Installed Next.js API routes for handling server-side logic.
Connected the project to MongoDB/Firebase for database operations.
Created basic schemas/models for:
🧑‍💼 Users (Account management)
🛋️ Products (Furniture & Crockery items)
🛒 Orders (Order history & tracking)
Defined RESTful API endpoints for CRUD operations.
Environment Variables
Configured a .env file for storing sensitive data:

plaintext
Copy
Edit
DATABASE_URL=<your_database_url>
API_KEY=<your_api_key>
Frontend Setup
Created reusable UI components:

🏠 Header/Navbar
📜 Footer
🎁 Product Card
Installed essential libraries:

📡 Axios/Fetch for API calls
🎨 Tailwind CSS for styling
Routing & Navigation
Implemented basic navigation using Next.js Router:

/ (🏠 Home)
/products (🛋️ Product Listings)
/cart (🛒 Shopping Cart)
/checkout (💳 Checkout)
Tech Stack Enhancements
Backend:
🖥 Framework: Next.js (API Routes)
📦 Database: MongoDB/Firebase
🔗 ORM/ODM: Mongoose/Prisma

Frontend:
🎨 Framework: React.js/Next.js
✨ Styling: Tailwind CSS

Installation
To test the updated technical foundation locally:

1️⃣ Clone the repository:

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone <your-repo-link>
2️⃣ Navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy
Edit
cd furniture-crockery-marketplace
3️⃣ Install backend and frontend dependencies:

bash
Copy
Edit
npm install
4️⃣ Run the backend server:

bash
Copy
Edit
npm run server
5️⃣ Start the frontend:

bash
Copy
Edit
npm run dev
Notes
⚠ Environment variables are critical. Never hardcode sensitive information.
✅ Test API routes using Postman or Thunder Client before full deployment.

